verbose_text: The elucidation of the pathogenesis from uncontrolled activation of the alternative complement pathway, resulting in formation of the membrane attack complex (MAC) C5b-9 8 has ultimately led to treatment with eculizumab, a monoclonal IgG antibody that binds to C5 and prevents subsequent formation of terminal complement 9.
evidence: IgG antibody that binds to C5 and prevents subsequent formation of terminal complement 9
